    <briefdescription>
<para>Slot info for fast sparse lookup - stores data pointer and linear index data pointer (8 bytes) is read/written atomically for thread-safety linearIdx is written BEFORE data on insert, so it&apos;s valid when data != nullptr Memory ordering: release on write, acquire on read - ensures linearIdx visible when data is. </para>
    </briefdescription>
